    "Management": {
      "text": "The following lacerations should be repaired by an oculoplastic specialist:\nLid margin\nOnly if >1mm; <1mm does not require suturing and will heal spontaneously\nWithin 6-8mm of medial canthus\nLacrimal duct or sac involvement\nInner surface of the lid involvement (or \"through and through\" laceration)\nWounds associated with ptosis\nTarsal plate or levator palpebrae muscle involvement\nSimple superficial horizontal lacerations may be repaired by the Emergency Physician\nAnesthesia:\nsupraorbital block\nor\ninfraorbital block\n.\n6-0 or 7-0\nsuture\nrecommended\nSutures should be removed in 5-7 days\nTetanus prophylaxis",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "supraorbital block",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Nerve_Block:_supraorbital"
        },
        {
          "text": "infraorbital block",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Nerve_Block:_Infraorbital"
        },
        {
          "text": "suture",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Sutures"
        },
        {
          "text": "Tetanus prophylaxis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Tetanus_prophylaxis"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "If repaired by the Emergency Physician, discharge with ophtho follow-up\nAll other lacerations require ophtho consult for repair",
